This paper deals with the problem of optimal control in Markov Decision Processes, which is a common topic in machine learning and artificial intelligence. The paper compares several approximate variations of the Policy Iteration algorithm, which is a popular reinforcement learning algorithm. Therefore, the most likely sub-categories are cs.LG (Machine Learning), cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), and cs.SY (Systems and Control). Additionally, the paper involves analysis of performance bounds and memory requirements, which could also fit into the sub-categories cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) and cs.RO (Robotics).
